<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870703-0149 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Mack Trucks Inc.</HL><DD> 07/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MACKBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   MACK TRUCKS INC. said it sold $215.1 million of asset-backed notes, the first in a proposed series of public offerings of as much as $450 million in notes. Proceeds from the sale will be used to pay bank debt and for capital spending, the Allentown, Pa.-based company said. The offering consisted of $103.7 million of 7.15% notes, priced at 99.9925 to yield 7.224% and $111.4 million of 8.13% notes at par. Shearson Lehman Brothers Inc. and Lazard Freres andamp; Co. are co-managers. </TEXT></DOC>